summary.para:
For instance, Entity.Rotation = new Vector(30f, 45f, 60f);, where the rotation order is the same as  in the setter of Entity.Rotation,
will set (almost) the same rotation as Entity.Quaternion = Quaternion.RotationAxis(Vector3.UnitZ, 60f * deg2Rad) * Quaternion.RotationAxis(Vector3.UnitX, 30f * deg2Rad) * Quaternion.RotationAxis(Vector3.UnitY, 45f * deg2Rad);
on condition that deg2Rad is calculated with (System.Math.PI / 180.0).

